-- Bear Stearns in talks to sell stake in firm: report
-- 
-- Wed Sep 26, 2007 4:15pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/26/us-bearstearns-sale-idUSWEN128420070926

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Bear Stearns is in serious talks with several outside investors, including Warren Buffett, about selling as much as 20 percent of the firm, according to a report in The New York Times online edition on Wednesday. 

 Citing people briefed on the discussions, the report said other investors who have expressed an interest in buying a minority stake include Bank of America, Wachovia and two Chinese institutions, the Citic Group and China Construction Bank. Bear Stearns shares were trading up about 11 percent at $127. Bear Stearns was not immediately available for comment.